Phase 4 — Add compliance-center variables safely

In your templates/ansible-molecule/template.yml, add an input like this:

aerolit_fixture_root:
  type: string
  default: ""

Then in the job variables, do not overwrite the real runner variable directly. Use an input variable:

variables:
  AEROLIT_FIXTURE_ROOT_INPUT: "$[[ inputs.aerolit_fixture_root ]]"

Then in your script section, add:

# Prefer explicit component input if provided.
# Otherwise use the runner-level AEROLIT_FIXTURE_ROOT environment variable.
if [ -n "${AEROLIT_FIXTURE_ROOT_INPUT:-}" ]; then
  export AEROLIT_FIXTURE_ROOT="$AEROLIT_FIXTURE_ROOT_INPUT"
fi
: "${AEROLIT_FIXTURE_ROOT:?AEROLIT_FIXTURE_ROOT is not set. Set it on the runner or pass aerolit_fixture_root to the component.}"
export AEROLIT_COLLECTION_HUB="${AEROLIT_COLLECTION_HUB:-$AEROLIT_FIXTURE_ROOT/hubs/current}"
export AEROLIT_TEST_FILES_DIR="${AEROLIT_TEST_FILES_DIR:-$AEROLIT_FIXTURE_ROOT/files/current}"
export AEROLIT_TEST_REPOS_DIR="${AEROLIT_TEST_REPOS_DIR:-$AEROLIT_FIXTURE_ROOT/repos/current}"

This makes the compliance component portable:

Your runner:
  gets AEROLIT_FIXTURE_ROOT from config.toml
Another program:
  can pass aerolit_fixture_root as a component input

