Phase 7 — Update molecule.yml to mount global fixtures

In templates/ansible-molecule/molecule.yml, add the file/repo mounts to every UBI platform.

Example:

volumes:
  - /sys/fs/cgroup:/sys/fs/cgroup:ro
  - ${AEROLIT_TEST_FILES_DIR}:/opt/aerolit/files:ro
  - ${AEROLIT_TEST_REPOS_DIR}:/opt/aerolit/repos:ro

So one platform becomes:

- name: ubi9
  image: ${UBI9_INIT_IMAGE}
  pre_build_image: true
  privileged: true
  command: /usr/sbin/init
  volumes:
    - /sys/fs/cgroup:/sys/fs/cgroup:ro
    - ${AEROLIT_TEST_FILES_DIR}:/opt/aerolit/files:ro
    - ${AEROLIT_TEST_REPOS_DIR}:/opt/aerolit/repos:ro
  tmpfs:
    /run: "rw"
    /tmp: "rw"

If you hit SELinux volume access issues later, change those fixture volume lines to:

    - ${AEROLIT_TEST_FILES_DIR}:/opt/aerolit/files:ro,z
    - ${AEROLIT_TEST_REPOS_DIR}:/opt/aerolit/repos:ro,z

Do not start there unless you need it.

