Phase 11 — Version control the Molecule toolchain

Molecule versions do matter. Molecule’s own docs say it supports only the latest two major versions of Ansible.   That does not mean you need to solve versioning before the fixture work, but once this works, do not leave the job floating forever with unpinned installs.

For now, print versions in every job. Later, create a pinned Molecule runner image.

The eventual direction should be an internal image like:

registry.gitlab.us.lmco.com:443/lit/containers/images/ansible-molecule-runner:2026.06

with a pinned set of:

python
ansible-core
molecule
molecule-plugins[podman]
ansible-lint
podman client
docker Python SDK only if you keep Docker fallback

Molecule plugins also matter because the plugin package has separate extras for drivers like Podman. The molecule-plugins project documents installing driver extras such as molecule-plugins[podman].  

